g" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Today is a very special day in my home -

It's my puppy PJ's 2nd birthday!!!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yQFD8Xs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I adopted him from Nashville Humane at only 3 months old and I severely underestimated how tough raising a puppy was.

Those first few months tested my patience, and there were many days where I wondered if I made a mistake.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5wEnAxm.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>But as he got older the vet allowed more and more exercise</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EuQAfcs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And I tried to expose him to as many environments as I could</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/weSmvLM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>He rode in that stroller all over Nashville until he was old enough to run, and then accomplished some pretty amazing things</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ybGdXh8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>At only one year of age, PJ ran his first two marathons, over 40 different half marathons, and...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6qkMePs.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Over 2,000 miles in one year!!!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/chqCKh5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>An insane year for my little 12lb buddy who loves nothing more than 3 hour runs and 3 hour cuddle sessions.

He has grown into the most loving and incredible friend over the last year.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qOGUjYC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Yesterday we celebrated Nanna's 16th birthday as we kicked off Puckett Week</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XlwrXyq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>7 days of fundraising and a Supply Drive for domestic violence survivors facing homelessness.

Look at how adorable @carlsaganforlife made little PJ, I love this image</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MlQKkE1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Domestic violence is the leading cause of homelessness among women and children in America. 

Last year on Imgur we raised over $30,000 worth of donations and goods for survivors!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aeeGnk6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Many survivors of abuse must face the terrifying decision of staying with their abuser or taking their kids or dogs to a homeless shelter. 

The Mary Parrish Center provides free housing, therapy, food and more to survivors - everything they might need to stay safe and start their life fresh again.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7az7xqZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Continuing the week of Nanna's 16th birthday and PJ's 2nd, I thought it would be nice if anyone who can afford it donate $16 to The Mary Parrish Center. 

I also had them set up an Amazon Wishlist if you'd like to send anything directly to the survivors in their new safe apartment.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6m3owpG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Adding PJ to the family was really tough at first, but I can't imagine being in a scenario where leaving an abuser could land us all homeless.

This week we can make the transition from abused and homeless to housed and loved just a little bit easier for domestic violence survivors. 

Happy birthday PJ and Nanna, let's do some good in your names this week.

...

To donate $16 -

https://www.maryparrish.org/donate

...

If you'd like to send goods to the survivors of domestic violence at Mary Parrish -

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/3USHUHIVSINQE?ref_=wl_share

...

Thank you for reading my post, I'll see everyone again tomorrow.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cYkVCm7</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MrPuckett]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Flawless execution</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/vQqnAD2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yEuPlTm.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/vQqnAD2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WeirdAlisMySpiritUserName]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>me like</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/EhtEgoc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/I9IOOdl.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/EhtEgoc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[reformedxile]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>KENT ENGLAND. PLEASE RESCUE THIS DOG</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/yHXlqyt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/N9I3eyw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://people.com/pets/dog-in-shelter-for-200-days-needs-home-after-valentines-day-party/ Dog in Shelter Over 200 Days Still Looking for a Home After No One Shows Up to Adoption Party</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/yHXlqyt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[songbird811]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Powerful</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WZ7ytQ5</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BtP9efT.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>#homeless #seattle #powerful #loveyourself</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/WZ7ytQ5</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MartyIndependence]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It's Borger Day at the Humane Society!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9bpASo9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https:/